Arrow Functions:

---Es6 version
---more readable and more structure
---annonymous functions(lambda functions)
---without function name but they are assigned to a variable

Example:

let C=()=>{
    code
}

Synchronous and asynchronous functions:

asynchronous founctions:

not a step by step process

use setTimeout(arrowFunctions only,time) built-in function
Example:

<script>
        console.log("hi raviteja")
        setTimeout(()=>{console.log("I am waiting")},5000)
        console.log("I am in lab")
</script>

callback function:
A call back function is a function that is passed argumnet to another function.

Example:

function greet(name, callback){
    console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`)
    callback()
}
function saygoodbye(){
    console.log("Goodbye")
}
greet("sam", saygoodbye)
